<paragraph id="404436B47607FFF74BBC8A5AFC1BF8F8" blockId="5.[136,897,1884,1911]" box="[136,897,1884,1911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">
<heading id="1B0C81D87607FFF74BBC8A5AFC1BF8F8" bold="true" box="[136,897,1884,1911]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" reason="1">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67607FFF74BBC8A5AFC1BF8F8" bold="true" box="[136,897,1884,1911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">
Original description (as 
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377607FFF74A9E8A5AFC8CF8F8" box="[426,790,1884,1911]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="schinzi" variety="maxima">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67607FFF74A9E8A5AFDE5F8F9" bold="true" box="[426,639,1884,1911]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Stauroneis schinzi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="728FEAA67607FFF7498D8A5AFC8CF8F8" bold="true" box="[697,790,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): 
<figureCitation id="D8C02A317607FFF748048A5AFC1BF8F8" box="[816,897,1884,1910]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–31" captionStartId="6.[136,243,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,190,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,190,1770]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–31. Stauroneis schinzii var. maxima Frenguelli. Figs 22. Original drawing of Frenguelli (1933, Pl. I, fig. 11). Figs. 23–28. LM. Specimens from type population. Fig. 24. Lectotype. Fig. 27. Detail of valve end showing distal raphe fissure. Note the thickened sternum. Fig. 28. Detail of valve centre showing sternum and proximal raphe ends. Figs 29–31. Specimen from type population. SEM. Fig. 29. Detail of internal valve end showing distal raphe end terminating in a weakly developed helictoglossa (arrow). Fig. 30. Detail of internal valve center showing proximal raphe ends and stauros. Fig. 31. Broken tilted valve in internal view. Scale bars: 10 µm (Figs 22–26, 31); 5 µm (Figs 27–30)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413102/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08E1653F7607FFF54BBC8AAEFF5EFE03" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph id="404436B47607FFF74BBC8AAEFE65F78B" blockId="5.[136,1452,1960,2054]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67607FFF74BBC8AAEFCBAF830" box="[136,800,1960,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">
Puede considerarse como una 
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377607FFF74A808AAEFDABF833" box="[436,561,1960,1981]" form="ligada" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" rank="form">forma ligada</taxonomicName>
a la variedad anterior [
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377607FFF748148AAFFC3EF830" box="[800,932,1960,1982]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="schinzii" variety="argentina">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67607FFF748148AAFFCDFF830" box="[800,837,1961,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">var.</emphasis>
argentina
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="728FEAA67607FFF748978AAFFE65F78B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">]; pero de dimensiones mucho mayores, de sílice más robusta, con extremos valvares menos atenuados, redondeados y con menor número de estrías. Valva: largo 0,294 a 0,308 ancho 0,026 a 0,027; estrías 11 en 0,01.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<caption id="1484663C7604FFF44BBC8A05FE22F843" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413102" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5413102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413102/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" startId="6.[136,243,1795,1817]" targetBox="[152,1436,190,1770]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="404436B47604FFF44BBC8A05FE22F843" blockId="6.[136,1452,1795,1997]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67604FFF44BBC8A05FEAFF896" bold="true" box="[136,309,1795,1817]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">FIGURES 22–31</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377604FFF44A758A05FD78F897" authority="Frenguelli." authorityName="Frenguelli." box="[321,738,1795,1817]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="schinzii" variety="maxima">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67604FFF44A758A05FE6CF896" box="[321,502,1795,1816]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Stauroneis schinzii</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="728FEAA67604FFF449128A02FDE8F897" box="[550,626,1796,1817]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">maxima</emphasis>
Frenguelli.
</taxonomicName>
Figs 22. Original drawing of 
<bibRefCitation id="246A4B457604FFF44F348A05FB39F896" author="Frenguelli, J." box="[1024,1187,1795,1817]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="365 - 476" refId="ref5815" refString="Frenguelli, J. (1933) Contribucion al conocimiento de las Diatomeas Argentinas. Diatomeas de la region de los Esteros del Ybera (en la Provincia de Corrientes). Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural Bernardino Rivadavia 37 (Protistologia 3): 365 - 476." type="journal article" year="1933">Frenguelli (1933</bibRefCitation>
, Pl. I, fig. 11). Figs. 23–28. LM. Specimens from type population. Fig. 24. Lectotype. Fig. 27. Detail of valve end showing distal raphe fissure. Note the thickened sternum. Fig. 28. Detail of valve centre showing sternum and proximal raphe ends. Figs 29–31. Specimen from type population. SEM. Fig. 29. Detail of internal valve end showing distal raphe end terminating in a weakly developed helictoglossa (arrow). Fig. 30. Detail of internal valve center showing proximal raphe ends and stauros. Fig. 31. Broken tilted valve in internal view. Scale bars: 10 µm (Figs 22–26, 31); 5 µm (Figs 27–30).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="404436B47605FFF54BBC8DA6FE76FF72" blockId="7.[136,1451,159,253]" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">
Here translated: 
<emphasis id="728FEAA67605FFF54A128D99FCF9FF3A" box="[294,867,159,181]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">
“It can be considered 
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377605FFF54ACE8DA6FDE0FF3A" box="[506,634,159,181]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" form="linked" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="126" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="form" species="anceps">a form linked</taxonomicName>
to the previous variety [
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377605FFF548578D99FC7FFF3B" box="[867,997,159,181]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="126" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="schinzii" variety="argentina">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67605FFF548578D99FC12FF3A" box="[867,904,159,180]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">var.</emphasis>
argentina
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="728FEAA67605FFF548D18D99FE76FF72" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">
], but with much higher valve dimensions, more heavily silicified, with less attenuated valve ends and lower stria number. Valve: length 0.294 a 0.308 [mm], width 0.026 a 0.027 [mm]; striae 
<quantity id="87039B517605FFF54A098DE1FEF7FF73" box="[317,365,231,253]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="7" pageNumber="126" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
0.01 [mm]”.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="404436B47605FFF54BBC8C2DFF5EFE03" blockId="7.[136,1452,299,397]" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">
Frenguelli recorded 
<taxonomicName id="87FB4D377605FFF54A458C2AFDE1FECB" box="[369,635,299,326]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stauroneidaceae" genus="Stauroneis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="126" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="schinzii" variety="maxima">
<emphasis id="728FEAA67605FFF54A458C2AFE7CFECB" box="[369,486,299,326]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">S. schinzii</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="728FEAA67605FFF549168C2AFDE1FECB" box="[546,635,300,325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as rare in Series 268. Our LM examination of the slides recovered 11 broken specimens of this variety. During SEM examination of Series 268 we found only one broken valve in internal view.
</paragraph>
